The paper deals with distributed optimization methods for networked agents, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. The use of randomized Gauss-Seidel iterations and Douglas-Rachford operators suggests a focus on numerical methods and algorithms, which is consistent with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with networked systems and coordination, which suggests a focus on distributed computing and control, consistent with the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and convergence, which suggests a focus on mathematical analysis and theory, consistent with the sub-category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
